Smoky Salsa Negra

1 c water
3 tbsp grated piloncillo or brown sugar
1 c vegetable oil
20 dried morita chiles, stemmed and seeded
1/4 c raw skinless peanuts
5 garlic cloves, unpeeled
3 tbsp minced ginger
3 tbsp apple cider vinegar
1 tbsp kosher salt

In a small saucepan, bring the water and the piloncillo to a boil. Remove from the heat and stir until the sugar is dissolved. Keep warm. In a medium saute pan, heat the oil over medium high heat. Add the chiles and stir to toast until fragrant, 2-3 min. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the chiles to the sugar water. To the pan of oil, add the peanuts and toast until fragrant, 3-4 min. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the peanuts to the sugar water. Add the garlic cloves to the pan next and cook, turning as needed, until charred, 2-3 min. Peel the skin off and add to the the sugar water with the minced ginger, vinegar, and salt. Transfer the whole mixture to a blender and puree until smooth. Can store in the refrigerator in an airtight container for up to 3 weeks.
